    "methodology": "Fatality and serious injury figures are from DfT STATS19 police-reported data. KSI rates use DfT traffic estimates for cycling miles. Infrastructure spend covers central government cycling and walking investment only; local authority co-funding is excluded. Regional rates use three-year rolling averages to smooth volatility from small numbers. Serious injury figures from 2017 onward use the revised CRASH severity adjustment and are not directly comparable with pre-2017 figures.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "CRASH severity adjustment introduced in 2016/17 means pre-2017 serious injury figures are not directly comparable",
      "Cycling miles estimates have wide confidence intervals due to small sample sizes in the National Travel Survey",
